(1985) Held that this section does not require agreement between the parties as a prerequisite of joint custody.  The court may order joint custody over the objection of a parent.  Goldberg v. Goldberg (A.), 691 S.W.2d 312.
(2024)  A modification seeking to give one parent final decision-making authority in the event the parties cannot agree on healthcare treatment is not a request to change the custody designation from joint legal custody to sole legal custody.  Schiesswohl v. Spain, 696 S.W.3d 907 (Mo.App.S.D.)
